# Exact-NS Tao Circuit Near-Closure Screening

Reusable findings for the Step-2 candidate screen and the completed Step-4
dossier, Step-5 repair verdicts, Step-6 readiness, the completed Step-6
freeze verdict, and the Step-7 guardrail freeze on the exact-NS
no-near-closed-Tao-circuit branch.

## Entries

- `all-promoted-step-2-candidates-share-one-five-role-exact-interaction-core.md`:
  all promoted candidates keep the same ordered exact role skeleton; what
  changes downstream is the gate, not the basic choreography.
- `all-promoted-step-2-candidates-share-the-same-forced-exact-ns-extras-around-the-core.md`:
  every promoted candidate must also carry the same mirror/conjugate,
  same-scale companion, long-leg feedback, and cross-scale next-shell extras.
- `template-defect-near-closure-compares-one-canonical-packet-to-one-fixed-five-channel-tao-template-on-one-window.md`:
  the first honest candidate notion compares one canonical role-labeled
  helical packet against one fixed five-channel Tao-like template on one
  declared finite activation window, using one invariant observable pair
  `(Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)` whose Step-3 invariant is pass/fail on the same
  coherently transported defect sheet rather than survival after retuning the
  role hierarchy, thresholds, or Tao-style gate freedoms.
  The completed audit now classifies it as `stable after canonicalization`.
  The post-repair shortlist now sharpens its admissibility sheet to
  `(1/4, 49/256)` and carries `F_SL(1/16)` as the Step-6 friendly stress
  witness.
- `windowed-spectator-leakage-budget-compares-off-template-mass-to-the-desired-five-channels-class-by-class.md`:
  a second candidate notion treats near-closure as a class-by-class leakage
  budget between off-template channels and the intended five-channel packet,
  with one hard sheet `(L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)`
  that stays meaningful only with the frozen spectator partition and
  `D_on`/`D_off` split.
  The completed audit now classifies it as `stable after canonicalization`
  and the cleanest obstruction-facing gate of the three.
  The post-repair shortlist now sharpens its admissibility sheet to
  `(1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24)` and carries
  `F_SS(1/12)` plus `F_SL(1/16)` as the Step-6 friendly stress set.
- `delayed-threshold-itinerary-fixes-one-exact-ordered-activation-sequence-with-predeclared-spectator-budgets.md`:
  a behavior-based candidate is only honest when it names one exact finite
  activation itinerary together with one ordered threshold sheet
  `(t_clk, t_trig, t_rot, t_next; sign sheet; spectator pass/fail)` and all
  spectator budgets on the same window; under whole-sheet scaling the honest
  invariant is the transported ordered event tuple, not raw unchanged
  timestamps on one display.
  The completed audit now classifies it as `use-case-limited but honest`, so
  it survives only as a narrow admission filter.
- `projection-rigidity-is-an-enforcement-mechanism-not-a-distinct-near-closure-candidate.md`:
  exact Leray / pressure projection enforces coefficient rigidity and
  spectator leakage for the three promoted candidates but does not define a
  separate near-closure object.
- `step-2-candidate-notions-must-freeze-packet-class-window-threshold-language-and-packet-sheet.md`:
  a Step-2 candidate is still a slogan until it fixes one packet class, one
  finite window, one threshold language, and one canonical packet sheet, and
  writes its interaction template and downstream gate on that same ledger.
- `step-3-robustness-only-quotients-a-narrow-exact-symmetry-tier-and-treats-later-sheet-drift-as-a-different-model.md`:
  Step-3 robustness may quotient only a narrow whole-sheet exact-symmetry tier;
  later spectator re-partitioning, threshold or window retuning, sign-sheet
  drift, packet regrouping, or imported Tao-style freedoms count as different
  candidate models rather than harmless rewrites.
- `step-4-is-well-posed-because-two-candidates-are-stable-after-canonicalization-and-the-third-remains-an-honest-admission-filter.md`:
  the completed Step-3 audit leaves Step 4 ready to proceed with leakage as
  the primary obstruction-facing gate, template defect as the primary
  theorem-facing gate, and the itinerary only as a narrow admission filter.
- `engineered-sign-sparse-triad-family-is-the-cleanest-friendly-step-4-witness-on-the-frozen-ledger.md`:
  `F_SS(mu)` is the cleanest friendly family on the frozen Step-4 sheet: all
  three promoted candidates pass on one engineered-sign sparse-triad ledger.
- `scale-separated-friendly-family-shows-the-remaining-ambiguity-is-event-trace-rigidity-not-leakage.md`:
  `F_SL(rho)` keeps template defect and leakage alive while the itinerary
  stays ambiguous because the exact `t_next` trace is not uniformly fixed,
  showing that the remaining bottleneck is event-trace rigidity rather than
  leakage failure.
- `step-5-is-well-posed-because-the-balanced-step-4-dossier-leaves-one-named-itinerary-repair.md`:
  the balanced anti/pro Step-4 dossier leaves template defect and leakage as
  honest survivors, reduces the itinerary to one named ambiguity, and makes
  Chain Step 5 an honest one-pass repair on the already frozen ledger.
- `step-5-repair-pass-is-controlled-by-the-final-step-4-result-plus-the-landed-pro-side-arithmetic.md`:
  the authorized Step-5 repair sheet is controlled by the final Step-4 result
  plus the landed pro-side arithmetic artifact, while the narrower
  intermediate anti note remains provenance and caution only.
- `template-defect-near-closure-honest-step-5-repair-tightens-thresholds-to-the-recorded-friendly-maxima.md`:
  the authorized template-defect repair removes unused slack by tightening
  `lambda_tmpl` to `1/4` and `lambda_spec` to `49/256`, preserving the same
  gate and hostile failure mechanism.
- `windowed-spectator-leakage-budget-honest-step-5-repair-tightens-budgets-to-the-recorded-friendly-maxima.md`:
  the authorized leakage repair tightens total, mirror, feedback, and cross
  budgets to the largest recorded friendly loads while leaving companion at
  the already-saturated `1/12`.
- `step-5-itinerary-split-leaves-only-an-early-admission-filter-and-no-honest-late-gate.md`:
  the authorized Step-5 split resolves the itinerary negatively: the early
  `pre-trigger delay filter` stays exact but too weak for the final shortlist,
  while the late `next-stage transfer-start filter` is not well-defined
  without softening the frozen late event language after outcomes are known.
- `step-6-is-well-posed-because-the-post-repair-shortlist-freezes-to-two-repaired-objects.md`:
  the completed Step-5 repair pass leaves exactly two repaired survivors on
  the frozen ledger, fully discards the itinerary route, and makes Step 6
  well posed with hostile `F_DT(delta, eta)` retained as the reference
  negative comparator.
- `step-6-freeze-keeps-repaired-template-defect-and-repaired-leakage-as-two-distinct-promoted-objects.md`:
  the completed Step-6 freeze promotes repaired template defect and repaired
  leakage unchanged as two distinct downstream objects, because the current
  dossier proves no implication in either direction and shared
  friendly/hostile outcomes are not an equivalence theorem.
- `template-defect-near-closure-step-6-next-test-is-the-carried-f-sl-rho-family-on-the-repaired-defect-sheet.md`:
  Step 6 should treat repaired template defect as a family-theorem setup on
  `F_SL(rho)`, `0 < rho <= 1/16`, on the same repaired defect gate, with an
  explicit missing-data ledger before any theorem-level upgrade.
- `windowed-spectator-leakage-budget-step-6-next-test-is-sharpness-of-the-repaired-sheet-on-the-friendly-stress-set.md`:
  Step 6 should treat repaired leakage as a sharpness/minimality test on the
  carried stress set `{F_SS(1/12), F_SL(1/16)}` on the same classwise sheet,
