Status: `INFERRED` Step-7 readiness synthesis from a `VERIFIED` frozen scorecard

After Step 1, the branch may claim only three things:
`F_SS(1/12)` is frozen on the canonical ledger,
one authoritative hard scorecard consisting of repaired `G_tmpl` and repaired
`G_leak` is frozen,
and the inherited static dossier already records that this witness passes
those two repaired gates on that same sheet.

After Step 1, the branch may not claim
exact closure,
finite closed-system isolation,
class retention under honest closure,
exact dynamic survival on `I = [0, 1]`,
itinerary success,
near-circuit behavior,
a mission-level counterexample,
or any broader transfer statement about `F_SL` or the whole one-bridge class.
Any later success remains witness-local unless a stronger transfer statement
is actually proved.

That no-overclaim rule makes the Step-2 verdict honest rather than rhetorical.
Step 2 can start because the witness and scorecard are now frozen sharply
enough to support one clean exact-closure audit, not because closure or
dynamics have already been earned.
So Step 2 begins as a forced-mode computation on the same frozen ledger, with
immediate branch failure if the computation requires class-changing additions,
arbitrary truncation, alternate currency, or other rescue logic.

