+# Step 8 Stops At Exact Non-Isolability Before Step-3 Dynamics On The Frozen Ledger
+
+Status: `INFERRED` constructive Step-8 verdict
+
+The current record already freezes the carried witness `F_SS(1/12)`,
+the canonical packet sheet,
+and one raw classwise closure-burden ledger.
+But it still does not freeze one finite support-level closure convention on
+that same ledger.
+
+Because of that gap, any attempt to write exact reduced dynamics would still
+require a forbidden after-the-fact choice:
+choosing a new explicit wavevector realization,
+deciding which mirror or shell-bridge companions to retain,
+or truncating the exact packet at a finite support boundary that the branch
+never froze.
+
+The earliest honest obstruction is therefore exact non-isolability on the
+frozen ledger, equivalently an arbitrary-truncation requirement before any
+exact reduced dynamics can be posed honestly.
+
+This is sharper than `more bookkeeping later`, but weaker than a proved class
+exit theorem or an uncontrolled packet-growth theorem.
+The current record does not yet identify one concrete class-changing forced
+mode, and it does not enumerate one infinite exact cascade of forced support
+modes.
+
+So the Step-8 branch-stop verdict is:
+class retention not earned,
+exact non-isolability / arbitrary truncation as the first constructive
+obstruction,
+and no Step-3 readiness because there is no finite exact closed system to
+inherit unchanged.
+
+Filed from:
